  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 350F (180C).",
    "Whisk together mustard, salt, pepper, lemon zest, and half a tablespoon of olive oil to make a light sauce.",
    "Coat the tuna pieces evenly with the mustard sauce and place them in an oven-safe dish.",
    "Scatter halved cherry tomatoes, chopped parsley, and mint over the fish.",
    "Pour 100ml water into the dish, then drizzle remaining olive oil on top.",
    "Cover the dish with foil and bake for 12 minutes, until the fish flakes easily.",
    "Remove foil, bake another 5 minutes to caramelize the tomatoes.",
    "Let rest 5 minutes, then serve hot, optionally garnished with extra parsley."
